SPEAKER: GENTLEWOMAN
TEXT: That, sir, which I will not report after her.

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: You may to me; and ’tis most meet you should.

SPEAKER: GENTLEWOMAN
TEXT: Neither to you nor anyone; having no witness to confirm my speech.

SPEAKER: GENTLEWOMAN
TEXT: Enter Lady Macbeth with a taper.

SPEAKER: GENTLEWOMAN
TEXT: Lo you, here she comes! This is her very guise; and, upon my life, fast

SPEAKER: GENTLEWOMAN
TEXT: asleep. Observe her; stand close.

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: How came she by that light?

SPEAKER: GENTLEWOMAN
TEXT: Why, it stood by her: she has light by her continually; ’tis her

SPEAKER: GENTLEWOMAN
TEXT: command.

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: You see, her eyes are open.

SPEAKER: GENTLEWOMAN
TEXT: Ay, but their sense are shut.

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: What is it she does now? Look how she rubs her hands.

SPEAKER: GENTLEWOMAN
TEXT: It is an accustomed action with her, to seem thus washing her hands. I

SPEAKER: GENTLEWOMAN
TEXT: have known her continue in this a quarter of an hour.

SPEAKER: LADY MACBETH
TEXT: Yet here’s a spot.

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: Hark, she speaks. I will set down what comes from her, to satisfy my

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: remembrance the more strongly.

SPEAKER: LADY MACBETH
TEXT: Out, damned spot! out, I say! One; two. Why, then ’tis time to do’t.

SPEAKER: LADY MACBETH
TEXT: Hell is murky! Fie, my lord, fie! a soldier, and afeard? What need we

SPEAKER: LADY MACBETH
TEXT: fear who knows it, when none can call our power to account? Yet who

SPEAKER: LADY MACBETH
TEXT: would have thought the old man to have had so much blood in him?

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: Do you mark that?

SPEAKER: LADY MACBETH
TEXT: The Thane of Fife had a wife. Where is she now?—What, will these hands

SPEAKER: LADY MACBETH
TEXT: ne’er be clean? No more o’ that, my lord, no more o’ that: you mar all

SPEAKER: LADY MACBETH
TEXT: with this starting.

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: Go to, go to. You have known what you should not.

SPEAKER: GENTLEWOMAN
TEXT: She has spoke what she should not, I am sure of that: heaven knows what

SPEAKER: GENTLEWOMAN
TEXT: she has known.

SPEAKER: LADY MACBETH
TEXT: Here’s the smell of the blood still: all the perfumes of Arabia will

SPEAKER: LADY MACBETH
TEXT: not sweeten this little hand. Oh, oh, oh!

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: What a sigh is there! The heart is sorely charged.

SPEAKER: GENTLEWOMAN
TEXT: I would not have such a heart in my bosom for the dignity of the whole

SPEAKER: GENTLEWOMAN
TEXT: body.

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: Well, well, well.

SPEAKER: GENTLEWOMAN
TEXT: Pray God it be, sir.

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: This disease is beyond my practice: yet I have known those which have

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: walked in their sleep, who have died holily in their beds.

SPEAKER: LADY MACBETH
TEXT: Wash your hands, put on your nightgown; look not so pale. I tell you

SPEAKER: LADY MACBETH
TEXT: yet again, Banquo’s buried; he cannot come out on’s grave.

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: Even so?

SPEAKER: LADY MACBETH
TEXT: To bed, to bed. There’s knocking at the gate. Come, come, come, come,

SPEAKER: LADY MACBETH
TEXT: give me your hand. What’s done cannot be undone. To bed, to bed, to

SPEAKER: LADY MACBETH
TEXT: bed.

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: Will she go now to bed?

SPEAKER: GENTLEWOMAN
TEXT: Directly.

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: Foul whisp’rings are abroad. Unnatural deeds

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: Do breed unnatural troubles: infected minds

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: To their deaf pillows will discharge their secrets.

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: More needs she the divine than the physician.—

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: God, God, forgive us all! Look after her;

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: Remove from her the means of all annoyance,

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: And still keep eyes upon her. So, good night:

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: My mind she has mated, and amaz’d my sight.

SPEAKER: DOCTOR
TEXT: I think, but dare not speak.

SPEAKER: GENTLEWOMAN
TEXT: Good night, good doctor.

SPEAKER: MACBETH
TEXT: To kiss the ground before young Malcolm’s feet,

SPEAKER: MACBETH
TEXT: And to be baited with the rabble’s curse.

SPEAKER: MACBETH
TEXT: Though Birnam wood be come to Dunsinane,

SPEAKER: MACBETH
TEXT: And thou oppos’d, being of no woman born,

SPEAKER: MACBETH
TEXT: Yet I will try the last. Before my body

SPEAKER: MACBETH
TEXT: I throw my warlike shield: lay on, Macduff;

SPEAKER: MACBETH
TEXT: And damn’d be him that first cries, “Hold, enough!”

SPEAKER: MACBETH
TEXT: Retreat. Flourish. Enter, with drum and colours, Malcolm, old Siward,

SPEAKER: MACBETH
TEXT: Ross, Thanes and Soldiers.

SPEAKER: MALCOLM
TEXT: I would the friends we miss were safe arriv’d.

SPEAKER: SIWARD
TEXT: Some must go off; and yet, by these I see,

SPEAKER: SIWARD
TEXT: So great a day as this is cheaply bought.

SPEAKER: MALCOLM
TEXT: Macduff is missing, and your noble son.

SPEAKER: ROSS
TEXT: Your son, my lord, has paid a soldier’s debt:

SPEAKER: ROSS
TEXT: He only liv’d but till he was a man;

SPEAKER: ROSS
TEXT: The which no sooner had his prowess confirm’d

SPEAKER: ROSS
TEXT: In the unshrinking station where he fought,

SPEAKER: ROSS
TEXT: But like a man he died.

SPEAKER: SIWARD
TEXT: Then he is dead?

SPEAKER: ROSS
TEXT: Ay, and brought off the field. Your cause of sorrow

SPEAKER: ROSS
TEXT: Must not be measur’d by his worth, for then

SPEAKER: ROSS
TEXT: It hath no end.

SPEAKER: SIWARD
TEXT: Had he his hurts before?

SPEAKER: ROSS
TEXT: Ay, on the front.

SPEAKER: SIWARD
TEXT: Why then, God’s soldier be he!

SPEAKER: SIWARD
TEXT: Had I as many sons as I have hairs,

SPEAKER: SIWARD
TEXT: I would not wish them to a fairer death:

SPEAKER: SIWARD
TEXT: And so his knell is knoll’d.

SPEAKER: MALCOLM
TEXT: He’s worth more sorrow,

SPEAKER: MALCOLM
TEXT: And that I’ll spend for him.

SPEAKER: SIWARD
TEXT: He’s worth no more.

SPEAKER: SIWARD
TEXT: They say he parted well and paid his score:

SPEAKER: SIWARD
TEXT: And so, God be with him!—Here comes newer comfort.

SPEAKER: SIWARD
TEXT: Enter Macduff with Macbeth’s head.

SPEAKER: MACDUFF
TEXT: Hail, King, for so thou art. Behold, where stands

SPEAKER: MACDUFF
TEXT: Th’ usurper’s cursed head: the time is free.

SPEAKER: MACDUFF
TEXT: I see thee compass’d with thy kingdom’s pearl,

SPEAKER: MACDUFF
TEXT: That speak my salutation in their minds;

SPEAKER: MACDUFF
TEXT: Whose voices I desire aloud with mine,—

SPEAKER: MACDUFF
TEXT: Hail, King of Scotland!

SPEAKER: ALL
TEXT: Hail, King of Scotland!

SPEAKER: MALCOLM
TEXT: We shall not spend a large expense of time

SPEAKER: MALCOLM
TEXT: Before we reckon with your several loves,

SPEAKER: MALCOLM
TEXT: And make us even with you. My thanes and kinsmen,

SPEAKER: MALCOLM
TEXT: Henceforth be earls, the first that ever Scotland

SPEAKER: MALCOLM
TEXT: In such an honour nam’d. What’s more to do,

SPEAKER: MALCOLM
TEXT: Which would be planted newly with the time,—

SPEAKER: MALCOLM
TEXT: As calling home our exil’d friends abroad,

SPEAKER: MALCOLM
TEXT: That fled the snares of watchful tyranny;

SPEAKER: MALCOLM
TEXT: Producing forth the cruel ministers

SPEAKER: MALCOLM
TEXT: Of this dead butcher, and his fiend-like queen,

SPEAKER: MALCOLM
TEXT: Who, as ’tis thought, by self and violent hands

SPEAKER: MALCOLM
TEXT: Took off her life;—this, and what needful else

SPEAKER: MALCOLM
TEXT: That calls upon us, by the grace of Grace,

SPEAKER: MALCOLM

TEXT: Whom we invite to see us crown’d at Scone.
